obo:GO_0005840 obo:IAO_0000115 An intracellular organelle, about 200 A in diameter, consisting of RNA and protein. It is the site of protein biosynthesis resulting from translation of messenger RNA mRNA. It consists of two subunits, one large and one small, each containing only protein and RNA. Both the ribosome and its subunits are characterized by their sedimentation coefficients, expressed in Svedberg units symbol: S. Hence, the prokaryotic ribosome 70S comprises a large 50S subunit and a small 30S subunit, while the eukaryotic ribosome 80S comprises a large 60S subunit and a small 40S subunit. Two sites on the ribosomal large subunit are involved in translation, namely the aminoacyl site A site and peptidyl site P site. Ribosomes from prokaryotes, eukaryotes, mitochondria, and chloroplasts have characteristically distinct ribosomal proteins.
